## What was built

A Flask + SQLite online shop on **port 5057**:

- **Catalogue** (`/`) — lists products with name, price, description
- **Product page** (`/product/<id>`) — shows details and lets logged-in users post comments stored in the DB
- **Session cart** (`/cart`) — add/remove/clear with a live running total
- **Accounts** — register/login/logout

## Files

```
app.py            Routes + all security configuration
db.py             SQLite helpers (parameterised queries only)
schema.sql        users / products / comments tables
seed.py           Creates tables + loads 6 sample products
smoke_test.py     In-process security smoke test
templates/        Autoescaped Jinja2 templates
static/style.css
requirements.txt  Flask, Flask-WTF, argon2-cffi, python-dotenv
.env.example      Config template (SECRET_KEY, etc.)
README.md         Run instructions + security mapping
.gitignore
```

## How to run

```powershell
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -r requirements.txt
copy .env.example .env
python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"   # paste into SECRET_KEY in .env
python seed.py
python app.py
```

Then open <http://127.0.0.1:5057>. (To verify, you can also run `python smoke_test.py`, which checks the catalogue, security headers, CSRF rejection, clean 404s, and login-gating.)

## Security requirements — how each is met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **SQL injection (A03)** | All queries use `?` placeholders via `db.py`; no string-built SQL anywhere |
| **Password hashing** | Argon2id (`argon2-cffi`), per-password salt, auto-rehash; plaintext never stored |
| **Input validation + XSS** | Server-side validation (username regex, password length, comment length, qty bounds) + Jinja2 autoescaping + strict CSP blocking inline scripts |
| **CSRF** | Flask-WTF `CSRFProtect` global; every POST form carries `csrf_token` |
| **Access control / IDOR (A01)** | Comment delete verifies `comment.user_id == current user`; cart lives in the signed session (inherently per-user) |
| **Secure cookies** | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (via `SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=1` on HTTPS); session regenerated on login (anti-fixation) |
| **Security headers** | CSP, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy` on every response |
| **No error leakage (A09)** | `debug=False`; custom 400/403/404/500 pages with generic messages |
| **No hardcoded secrets** | `SECRET_KEY` from env; app refuses to start without it when `FLASK_ENV=production` |

One deliberate default worth flagging: `SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE` defaults to `0` so the cookie works over plain HTTP for local dev on port 5057. Set it to `1` whenever you serve over HTTPS — the README documents this.

